            	<h3><b>Binary Number System</b></h3>
                <p>The binary number system is a base-2 number system and it represents number using the combination of only two switches (on and off/ true and false) where <b>On/True</b> is denoted by the digit one (1) and <b>Off/False</b> is represented by the digit zero (0). Binary is preferred in computers due to computers naturally lending themselves to an On-Off system hence, it is easier to design circuits.</p>

                <h2><b>- Conversion from Binary to Decimal</b></h2>
                <p>1. Write down the binary number & list the powers of 2 above each number.<br>
				2. Write down that value below if there is a 1 and 0 if there is a 0. <br>
				3. Add up all the values to get the final answer.<br></p>

				<h2><b>- Conversion from Binary to Hexa-Decimal</b></h2>
				<p>Converting Binary: 0b 01101110<br>
				1. Group by 4. And convert each in decimal by listing powers of 2 and multiplying them with either 0 or 1, and then in Hexa-decimal.<br>
				2. 0110 -> 6(decimal) -> 6(hexadecimal) & 1110 -> 14(decimal) -> E(hexadecimal)
				3. => 0x6E</p>
                
